@Vhenom wrote:

[quote=“fasthop10, post:2, topic:415981”]first try removing the code you entered and run client to check if it fixes the problem.

then do what it says close the client and close java itself in task manager.

if not that , means there is an issue in your code. check file names and directory names for an issue. double check your interface to see if it compatible with your client.

if your creating a new interface i recommend lins interface maker.
